# Cursor Rule: Date Handling Best Practices

## ALWAYS
- Always generate all date stamps in documentation or code updates using a JavaScript utility script (e.g., new Date().toISOString()), not manually or by the AI assistant.
- Always use a utility script or function to insert the current date/time.
- Always call the script and insert the output when updating docs.

## NEVER
- Never hardcode or guess dates in docs or code comments.

## Example
```js
const now = new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0];
// Use 'now' for date stamps in docs
```

